node.text:
Last month we shared a story about a good boy named Happy who was hit by a car down in Texas and Maxine and I asked for your support to help fund Happy’s Surgery. Well we’re proud to announce that because of you, Happy got the surgery he needed, and he’s recovering and loving life with his new parents.

And this month, Maxine and I would like to bring your attention to another good girl who desperately needs our help.

This is Edith. And Edith was almost euthanized due to overcrowding at a shelter down in South Texas, before being saved by the Lucky Lab Rescue. Unfortunately Edith contracted Parvo, a horrible virus that can be fatal to dogs who are not fully vaccinated. Edith is currently in the ER on round the clock care, and with your help, she can have a good chance of beating Parvo so she can get adopted into her forever home.

If you want to read more about Edith, or donate to help her fight Parvo, we have a link in our bio where you can do that.

Every month, we’re going to be sharing these stories of pets who need our help, in partnership with the incredible folks at @waggleforpets , who are the only pet dedicated crowdfunding platform that work directly with pet owners, shelters, and leading veterinary providers to make sure that 100% of your donations go directly to the pet’s medical care.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by 🐶 Maxine the Fluffy Corgi on July 26, 2021. May be an image of dog and text that says 'In 2019, Maxine had surgery to repair a shoulder tear and remove bone spurs in her forelimbs, which occurred as a result of elbow osteoarthritis, which she's had since she was a puppy. Unfortunately this is very common in short-legged dogs like Maxine.'.

Welcome to the Little Chonk Space Jam. Who wants to join the Chonk Squad? @Superchewer #Superchewer #ad

The ONLY subscription box we have for Maxine is the Superchewer box.  Every month we get a themed box with some incredible toys that are made for monster chewers like Maxine.  They’re thoughtfully designed and are the only toys that last in our house.  We can’t recommend it enough.  If you want to try the Superchewer box, click the link in our bio to get this Space Jam box and $84 of FREE toys.  Chew on, my chonky friends.
